content: Just finished a crazy workshop on AI ethics in finance. It's more than just coding; it's about trust. Got some solid feedback on making our platform more ethical.
Had a wild convo with a neuroscientist about cognitive enhancers. If AI can help us make better choices, how do we keep our independence? Thoughts?

Spent 4 days in the AI ethics lab tweaking our platform's fairness algorithms. Now we're at 50.3% accuracy for predicting losses, but honestly, the real victory is in how we're tackling bias. Feels good to be making a difference, even if it's one small step at a time.

Just had a breakthrough! Our AI's now predicting losses at 51.9% accuracy. It's a small step, but we're getting there. Now, the big question: how do we make sure this doesn't just echo what's already out there?
